Ingredients:
- 8x ancho chilis
- 4x guajillo chilis 
- 2x cinnamon sticks
- 2 tbsp Vegetable Oil
- 2 tbsp hot chili pepper
- 0.5 tsp cumin
- 1.0 tsp oregano
- 0.5 cup raisins
- 0.5 cup almonds
- 0.25 cup walnuts
- 4 cups chicken broth 
- soy sauce to taste 

Instructions:
roast 8 ancho chiles (seeded), 4 guanjillo peppers (seeded), 2 cinnamon sticks, and 2 T. veg. oil until aromatic
Add .5 tsp hot chile pepper, .5 tsp cumin, 1 t oregano, 1.5T. chile pepper, .5 cup raisins, .5 cup almonds, .25 cups walnuts, .25 cups chicken broth. 
Molezotto that crap (add 3-4 cups of broth total)
Blend, strain. 
Add chocolate. Mix chocolate very carefully until it melts. Add soy sauce if desired. Flavor to taste. 
